-- Agrifirma Brazil Eyes Hong Kong Public Offering, Financial Time Reports
-- Victoria Batchelor
-- 2010-07-18T23:47:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-18/agrifirma-brazil-eyes-hong-kong-public-offering-financial-time-reports.html

          
          
             Agrifirma Brazil, a business backed
by Jacob Rothschild, is hoping to become the first Brazilian
company to list on the Hong Kong stock exchange, the Financial
Times reported, citing Chairman Ian Watson. The company, which
buys scrubland and transforms it into farmland, has raised $179
million to date, including investments from Hong Kong
businessmen Raymond Kwok and Adrian Fu and from investment group
Lake House, the FT said.  
